               <p>Mr. Mendez de Costa depos'd, That he having been Abroad, when he came Home, upon enquiry, found that the Prisoner, who had gone out with him behind the Coach, had been at Home, and was gone; upon which, going to the Scriptore, found that the Things mentioned in the Indictment were missing; that he sent after him divers Ways, to Dover, Harwich, &amp;c. and that the Prisoner was taken at Canterbury, viewing the Cathedral.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17300408-57-person319">
                  John 
                  Pisin 
               <interp inst="t17300408-57-person319" type="surname" value="Pisin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17300408-57-person319" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17300408-57-person319" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             depos'd, That he being sent in pursuit of the Prisoner, found him in Canterbury, with the Diamond Ring, and other Things in his Pocket, and that upon his being apprehended, he confess'd he had taken them out of the Scriptore; that he found the Spoons and Forks, at a Goldsmiths at Canterhury , where he had offer'd them to sale.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17300408-57-person320">
                  Christopher 
                  Simpkins 
